Got to lose to win.
-
Ever notice when you lose a bunch all of a sudden amazing things happen?
-
Well that’s life and that’s success.
-
In order to win you have to lose. Even the most successful people lose to this day. 
-
When you’re on a losing streak switch your mind to “hell yeah this means something badass is about to happen!!”
-
See you only look at success and never look at all the failures that happen before the success happened.
-
Lose, Lose, Lose and then there’s the WIN!!!
-
Next time you’re losing think differently about it and each loss is the next step to success. You will start to like the losses a little more and you will appreciate the wins that much more.
-
Fucking life is crazy but damn it’s a good time, live it, embrace it and DRIVE HEAD ON!!!

Watching others on Social Media living life.

It’s always been crazy to me how people can watch others on Social Media live a badass life yet they stay right where they are in life.

What I’m saying is, “don’t allow your mind to settle cause you think that’s all it can settle for.”

You can also go live a badass life and you can live it wherever you choose to live it.

Lock yourself down.

What I mean by “lock yourself down” is finally take a year and focus on you for once.

There will always come a time in everyone’s life where you will have to ignore everything and anything that distracts you from what you want to do.

The party’s have to stop, going to bars/clubs needs to stop, hanging with your friends (which btw are probably fucking losers) has to stop, the family gatherings has to stop, if your partner in your relationship doesn’t support you or these things you want to do needs to stop and has to be removed.

These are facts, this is the fucking truth and how I know this is the truth is because I had to do all these things.

Yes I ended friendships, yes I ended relationships, yes I stopped family gatherings, yes I ended everything if it didn’t help me with my goals in life that I wanted to achieve.

Oh and you will feel alone during this lockup, but that’s the fucking point you need to be alone because you need to help yourself first before you can help others.

So put a lock on the door and say goodbye because this is your time to start doing some real hard time. You will come out a better person and a more driven person at that.

No more comfort because this bullshit comfort life you’re living is not doing you any justice.

So here’s the story, yesterday I decided to go to Fossil Creek in Arizona, a place y’all all most go see.

I hiked down a massive canyon that is 4 miles down to get to Fossil Creek and then 4 miles back up the canyon to get back. 

It was an incredible time and I have a ton of content to share with you all.

Once I got to the bottom I decided to dive in the water, something I typically do even in my shallow pool. Btw probably not the smartest thing to do but typical me I like doing dumb shit lol.

I had no idea there was a huge log in the water, everything looked very clear to me so I dove in and BAM straight to the head.

After it happen 5 nurses just so happen to be walking down and saw what happen.

Straight up angels in my eyes. They took a look and I applied pressures until bleeding stopped. They gave me some electrolyte tablets and took a shirt ripped it up and wrapped my head.

It was nice having them for reassurance so thank you to all of you for helping me. 

The problem now was the 4 mile hike back up this massive canyon with no cell phone service.

I knew if I made the hike back up my head wasn’t that bad and it was just a deep cut.

So I thought out a game plan and headed up this 4 mile hike to the top.

Anytime I felt too much pressure I stopped for a little in the shade. After 4 miles of hiking back up this massive canyon I felt fine and went to an Urgent Care in Payson AZ. 

26 stitches, a tetanus shot and back on my feet!!!

Thank you Doctor Mike and your crew y’all were super cool. 

Life knocks you down but you gotta get back up, it’s how it’s been ever since my motorcycle wreck in 2016 when I started the road rash line and revamped @thedriveclothing 💀

It’s seems it’s destined for me to always get kicked down physically but I know god wants me around to show people how to get back up.

I’ll always continue to rise and show that drive!!!

Thank you to all the support you have shown me and my brand it means the world to me and I’ll be sticking around so don’t y’all worry hahaha.🤜🤛

Struggles, hate and temptations. 
-
As we go down new paths in life we will always run into those three words above, but here is the positivity in these three words. 
-
The Struggle - be thankful for the struggles you go through. They make you stronger, humble and wiser. Don’t let them break you. Let them make you.👊🏻
-
The Hate - they hate cause they ain’t you, they hate cause they are scared to do what you do, they hate because what you’re doing is not what society tells us to do, they hate because they are bored, they hate because it would be to hard for them, the hate is great because it’s the gasoline to light the fire underneath you.🔥 
-
Use it and drive forward but never hate back. Pay more attention to the ones that support you because not everyone will like you.👊🏻
-
The Temptations - these temptations are something I personally love, I have personally laid cookies around me just to make me stronger. Yes lay it all out and say to yourself “I am stronger than a fucking cookie.”🍪 
-
Don’t let a cookie ruin your goal, for goodness sack it’s a fucking cookie, you are stronger than a cookie right??!? Surround yourself with temptations to make you stronger and when those cookies aka temptations show up later on you will simply laugh and move along.😏👊🏻
-
Give yourselves the benefit of doubt, your mind is much stronger than you think it is.
-
If you need help DM me I’ll show you how strong your mind really is.
